result.execSummary:
The defendant David M. Winarski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Materials for Manufacturing Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater, Second and Subsequent Offense], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.65.
  • Manufacturing Methamphetamine(<=3g) [Modifiers: Repeater, Second and Subsequent Offense], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)1.
  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place [Modifiers: Repeater, Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.
